{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":92317,"duration_api_ms":85803,"num_turns":21,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"99d1f6c8-38c7-48d4-8887-2ee8162be385","total_cost_usd":0.4185365,"usage":{"input_tokens":11,"cache_creation_input_tokens":31086,"cache_read_input_tokens":277438,"output_tokens":3419,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":31086,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":11,"outputTokens":3419,"cacheReadInputTokens":277438,"cacheCreationInputTokens":31086,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.4185365,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"evidence":["The helper `agent_record_producer(&InvocationMetadata) -> RecordProducer` is correctly defined in `src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs:197-202`, extracting `backend_used.family` and `model_used.model_id` from the invocation envelope metadata.","All four persistence call-sites (prompt_review, completion, final_review, engine single-stage) now return the producer from the envelope metadata via the helper instead of reconstructing it from the resolved target: `prompt_review.rs:320`, `completion.rs:279`, `final_review.rs:861`, `engine.rs:4649`.","The internal invoke functions (`invoke_panel_member`, `invoke_completer`, `invoke_final_review_member`) have updated return types from `AppResult<Value>` to `AppResult<(Value, RecordProducer)>`, propagating the metadata-derived producer to each call-site.","All callers correctly destructure the new tuple return value (6 call-sites across `prompt_review.rs`, `completion.rs`, `final_review.rs`).","The `ArtifactRecord` struct in `src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs:330` already carries `producer: Option<RecordProducer>` — no struct changes were needed.","The conformance scenario in `scenarios.rs:10637-10648` now asserts that serialized `RecordProducer::Agent` includes both `backend_family` and `model_id` fields.","Unit test `agent_record_producer_uses_invocation_metadata_fields` passes (`cargo test --lib`), confirming the helper correctly maps metadata fields.","All 12 `workflow_composition` tests pass. All 5 `final_review_` tests pass.","`cargo check` compiles cleanly with no errors.","Remaining `backend.family.to_string()` / `model.model_id.clone()` usages in workflow_composition are for unrelated structs (`ResolvedTargetRecord`, `ReviewerProposalRecord`, invocation request construction) — not for `RecordProducer::Agent`.","`RecordProducer::Agent` is now constructed in exactly 3 places: the centralized helper (mod.rs:198), the unit test assertion (mod.rs:228), and the conformance test (scenarios.rs:10628). No production code directly constructs it anymore."],"findings_or_gaps":["Outstanding risk acknowledged by implementer: `AgentExecutionService` normalizes `backend_used`/`model_used` to the resolved target before orchestration reads the envelope, so `backend_used` currently always equals the resolved target. The refactoring is correct and prepares for when adapters report divergent metadata, but there is no end-to-end test yet that demonstrates divergent adapter-reported metadata flowing into persisted artifacts. This is a pre-existing limitation, not a regression.","The `--quiet` flag with `cargo test` (without `--lib`) did not match the test — this is a cargo test binary vs lib test discrepancy, not a code issue. Test passes correctly with `--lib`."],"follow_up_or_amendments":[],"outcome":"approved"},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"372b11d9-b39d-447f-961d-5928c525f47b"}
